


Standard Error Stream---Brief Messages "estream_put_bullet.h"

    Macros

            The macros

                    ESTREAM_BULLET_ERROR
                    ESTREAM_BULLET_WARNING and
                    ESTREAM_BULLET_NOTE
            
            are each defined as string literals. Their
            intended use is to be sent to the standard error
            stream as prefixes to error, warning, and note
            messages, respectively.

    Functions

        The estream_put_bullet Function

            The estream_put_bullet function writes the
            standard error stream, on its own line, the
            prefix specified by #0, followed by the message
            specified by #1.
              If #0 is less than zero, the message is
            considered a warning; otherwise, if #0 is equal
            to zero, the message is considered a note;
            otherwise, the message is considered an error
            message.
              The estream_put_bullet function returns a
            negative value, indicating atypical behavior, if
            #0 is negative; zero, indicating success,
            if #0 is zero; otherwise a positive value,
            indicating an error.
